Attention! Contest! Over past several years, inspired by Instagram, we saw lots of beautiful places and now want to offer you to discover new horizons! Paris, London or maybe Rome or Berlin? We are starting new project in which every month everyone can have the chance to win @aeroflot plane tickets!
To participate in the competition you have to make the following steps:
1). Follow (don't worry, you won't have to sign up for dozens of accounts üòâ) @katia_mi, @katia_mi_ and @atmolex.
2). Mention 3 of your friends in the comments below this post.
3). Repost the photo above or post your own favorite photo from your travels.
4). Tag @katia_mi, @katia_mi_ and @atmolex on the photo you posted.
5). Write in the caption to the photo that you are participating in #katia_mi_contest, mention @katia_mi, @katia_mi_ and @atmolex and tell us which country do you want to visit and why.
6). Make sure your Instagram profile is opened to public.
7). Photos posted during the contest period mentioned below will be the only ones to be considered. The number of photos of each participant is not limited.
üòé. The prize draw will be permitted only to those participants who have fulfilled all the conditions of the contest.
9). Photos and/or repost must be placed in the period from 28.04.17 to 20.05.17. The contest results will be announced on 21.05.17. The winner will be chosen at random from 15 best photos selected by organizers and published in Instagram Storis of @katia_mi, @katia_mi_ and @atmolex.
10). The winner will be given one or more tickets for a total amount of 30 000 Russian Roubles or equivalent in USD or Euros.
11). To participate in the competition you have to be 18 years or older.
We will contact the winner sending DM to Instagram account and the copy to email address, if mentioned in the profile. The winner will be kindly asked to reply to the message within 2 weeks, if not ‚Äì we will have to choose the new winner.

Dear friends! Recently, at the invitation of our friends from R√ºsselsheim we went to new Opel Insignia test drive in wonderful city of Frankfurt and surrounding area. Design of the car impressed me a lot. It's largely based on Monza concept presented in 2013. Design team headed by Mark Adams combined flowing lines and subtle surfaces with crisp, precise lines to even exaggerate the dramatic proportions. As the result the car looks longer, lower and wider than it actually is, and it definitely looks upscale. Every design feature conveys technical know-how and utmost precision!

Did you know that cats wag their tails when faced with a choice. It means that one desire is blocking another. For example, if the cat is in the doorway and wants to leave but it's raining on the street the tail will swing due to the internal conflict. The cat wants to go out but don't want to get wet. As soon as it decides whether to stay home or go out in the rain, the tail will immediately stop swinging!
